'''子彈蟻'''（[[学名|学名]]：''{{lang|la|Paraponera clavata}}''）是一種[[螞蟻|螞蟻]]，只居住在[[中南美洲|中南美洲]]。

子彈蟻的體型可超過2.5公分，是世界上體形最大的螞蟻之一。由於被兇狠的針一下的話就會感受到好像被[[子彈|子彈]]打到的那種疼痛，被冠以子彈蟻這樣的稱呼。子彈蟻能掠食像小型[[蛙|蛙]]的獵物，即使只有一隻也可以捕食比自身大好幾倍的昆蟲。唯一的剋星是比較小的[[寄生蠅|寄生蠅]]。牠也是世界上被咬到最痛的昆蟲。

[[巴西|巴西]][[亞馬遜州|亞馬遜州]]的[[Mawé族|Mawé族]]原住民會將子彈蟻放入竹編手套，用於[[成年禮|成年禮]]儀式中。<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.thesundaytimes.co.uk/sto/travel/Holidays/Wildlife/article77936.ece | work=The Sunday Times | location=London | title=Bitten by the Amazon | first=Steve | last=Backshall | date=6 January 2008 | accessdate=21 May 2010 | archive-date=2014-02-22 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222144437/http://www.thesundaytimes.co.uk/sto/travel/Holidays/Wildlife/article77936.ece | dead-url=no }}</ref>

== 描述 ==
工蟻的體長約為 {{convert|18|–|30|mm|in|1|abbr=on}}<ref name=brown>{{Cite journal| author1 = Brown | first1 = B. V.| author2 = Feener | first2 = D. H.| title = Behavior and Host Location Cues of Apocephalus paraponerae (Diptera: Phoridae), a Parasitoid of the Giant Tropical Ant, Paraponera clavata (Hymenoptera: Formicidae)| url = https://archive.org/details/sim_biotropica_1991-06_23_2/page/182 | jstor = 2388304| journal = Biotropica| volume = 23| issue = 2| pages = 182–187| year = 1991| doi = 10.2307/2388304}}</ref>，外型類似帶有紅色光澤的黑色粗壯無翼[[黃蜂|黃蜂]]。子彈蟻為[[掠食者|掠食者]]，和其他較原始的[[螞蟻|螞蟻]]一樣，牠們的工蟻不具有[[多態性_(生物學)|多態性]]，而[[蟻后|蟻后]]的體型也沒有較工蟻大<ref>{{cite web|last1=Morgan|first1=Randy C.|title=Giant Tropical Bullet Ant, Paraponera clavata, Natural History and Captive Management|url=http://www.sasionline.org/antsfiles/pages/bullet/bulletbio.html|website=Sonoran Arthropod Studies Institute|accessdate=June 10, 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090323040513/http://www.sasionline.org/antsfiles/pages/bullet/bulletbio.html|archivedate=2009-03-23|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。子彈蟻並非侵略性強的物種，但是牠們會極力保衛牠們的蟻窩，透過{{link-en|鳴喘發音|stridulation}}發出警告並利用[[螫針|螫針]]攻擊入侵者<ref name="SciELO">{{cite journal |last=Haddad |first=Vidal |date=2005 |title=Description of an injury in a human caused by a false tocandira (Dinoponera gigantea, Perty, 1833) with a revision on folkloric, pharmacological and clinical aspects of the giant ants of the genera Paraponera and Dinoponera (sub-family Ponerinae) |journal=[[SciELO|SciELO]] |volume=47 |issue=4 |issn=1678-9946 |url=http://www.scielo.br/scielo.php?script=sci_arttext&pid=S0036-46652005000400012 |access-date=2019-04-14 |archive-date=2021-03-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210308141116/http://www.scielo.br/scielo.php?script=sci_arttext&pid=S0036-46652005000400012 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

